# General Software Development Guidelines

## Overview
This document provides a set of best practices and principles for developing high-quality software within the Cursor ecosystem. It aims to ensure consistency, maintainability, and scalability across the codebase.

## Core Principles
- Maintain clear, readable, and self-documenting code.
- Incorporate automated testing and continuous integration.
- Adhere to coding standards and style guidelines.
- Use version control effectively with meaningful commit messages.

## Code Quality
- Write modular, reusable, and efficient code.
- Follow SOLID principles and appropriate design patterns.
- Document code and APIs using established documentation standards.

## Review and Collaboration
- Conduct regular code reviews.
- Ensure knowledge sharing and maintain updated documentation.
- Use collaborative tools to track issues and progress.

## Additional Considerations
- Prioritize security, performance, and scalability.
- Keep dependencies updated and manage technical debt proactively. 
